quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  93,1,"By the bright forenoon,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  93,2,"and by the night when it covers the world with peace:"{1},footnotes:1:1
  93,3,"(O Prophet), your Lord has neither forsaken you, nor is He displeased."{1},footnotes:1:1
  93,4,"Indeed what is to come will be better for you than what has gone by."{1},footnotes:1:1
  93,5,"Verily your Lord will soon give you so amply that you will be well-pleased."{1},footnotes:1:1
  93,6,"Did He not find you an orphan and then gave you shelter?"{1},footnotes:1:1
  93,7,"Did He not find you unaware of the Right Way, and then directed you to it?"{1},footnotes:1:1
  93,8,"And did He not find you in want, and then enriched you?"{1},footnotes:1:1
  93,9,"Therefore, be not harsh with the orphan;"{1},footnotes:1:1
  93,10,"and chide not him who asks,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  94,1,"(O Prophet), Did We not lay open your breast"{1},footnotes:1:1
  94,2,"and relieve you of the burden"
  94,3,"that had well-nigh broken your back?"{1},footnotes:1:1
  94,4,"And did We not exalt your fame?"{1},footnotes:1:1
  94,5,"Indeed, there is ease with hardship."
  94,6,"Most certainly, there is ease with hardship."{1},footnotes:1:1
  94,7,"So, whenever you are free, strive in devotion,"
  94,8,"and turn to your Lord with longing."{1},footnotes:1:1